sec.p:
In accordance with Article 43 of Regulation (EC) No 396/2005, in October 2023, EFSA was therefore mandated by the European Commission, to provide a statement on the review of the MRLs for copper compounds of Regulation (EC) No 396/2005 and the proposed new MRLs for copper compounds assessed by EFSA in 2020 and 2022, but not yet implemented in EU legislation by:
Updating the occurrence 8 data considered in the reasoned opinion on the MRL review for copper with occurrence data received by EFSA until 2022 across all regulatory domains (ToR 1);
Considering all MRL applications for which reasoned opinions under Article 10 are already published, but not yet implemented in EU legislation, and review their conclusions (ToR 2);
Updating the exposure assessment performed in the 2023 EFSA scientific opinion to understand whether new data have an impact on the previous exposure calculations (ToR 3);
Updating the table of MRLs included in the EFSA Reasoned Opinion on the review of the MRLs for copper compounds under Article 12 of Regulation (EC) No 396/2005, deriving 2 lists of MRLs: a list of MRLs calculated from the updated occurrence data and a list of MRLs as derived from the residue trials supporting the existing uses, and providing recommendations (ToR 4).

EFSA has based its assessment on the following documents:
EFSA's scientific opinion on the re‐evaluation of the existing health‐based guidance values (HBGVs) for copper and exposure assessment from all sources (EFSA Scientific Committee, 2023);
EFSA's reasoned opinions on the modification of the existing MRLs for copper compounds in fresh herbs and edible flowers (EFSA, 2020) and in other small fruits and berries (EFSA, 2022) and the supporting evaluation reports (Austria, 2022; Germany, 2018);
EFSA's reasoned opinion on the review of the existing MRLs for copper compounds (EFSA, 2018b) and the supporting Evaluation report (France, 2016);
Evaluation reports submitted by Member States during the additional ad hoc MS consultation (Austria, 2024; Czech Republic, 2024; Germany, 2024; Italy, 2024a, 2024b; Poland, 2023; Spain, 2024);
Data collected within EFSA's annual Chemical Monitoring data collection as described in the text of this statement.

For MRLs derived from residue trials supporting the existing uses (list 2), the MRLs proposed during the Article 12 review were not recalculated but reported as such in the recommendation table (Table 5) of this statement, except for:
plums, head cabbages, beans (with pods), beans (without pods), peas (with pods), peas (without pods), lentils (fresh) and sugar beets for which new trials submitted under the ad hoc consultation and compliant with the authorised uses already assessed during the MRL review were used to derive more robust MRLs and;
citrus fruits, table olives, kaki, granate apples, beetroots, carrots, celeriacs, horseradishes, Jerusalem artichokes, parsnips, parsley roots, radishes, salsifies, swedes, turnips, garlic, onions, shallots, Brussels sprouts, Chinese cabbages, kales, kohlrabies, celeries, Florence fennels, rhubarbs, peas (dry), olives for oil production and wheat, for which additional uses authorised after the MRL review and the supporting residue trials were submitted under the ad hoc consultation.
